cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of logic-based systems for answer-set programming, which is a subfield of AI. 
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper introduces a new logic, PS+, which is based on propositional schemata and the Closed World Assumption. This falls under the scope of logic in computer science. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper presents a programming system based on the logic PS+ and discusses its implementation and performance. This is relevant to the subfield of programming languages. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper characterizes the class of problems that can be solved by finite PS+ theories, which involves analyzing the complexity of algorithms. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents a solver for processing theories in PS+ and discusses its performance results, which are relevant to software engineering.
